33namespace {
34constexpr TimeDelta kBweIncreaseInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(1000);
35constexpr TimeDelta kBweDecreaseInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(300);
36constexpr TimeDelta kStartPhase = TimeDelta::Millis(2000);
37constexpr TimeDelta kBweConverganceTime = TimeDelta::Millis(20000);
38constexpr int kLimitNumPackets = 20;
39constexpr DataRate kDefaultMaxBitrate = DataRate::BitsPerSec(1000000000);
40constexpr TimeDelta kLowBitrateLogPeriod = TimeDelta::Millis(10000);
41constexpr TimeDelta kRtcEventLogPeriod = TimeDelta::Millis(5000);
42// Expecting that RTCP feedback is sent uniformly within [0.5, 1.5]s intervals.
43constexpr TimeDelta kMaxRtcpFeedbackInterval = TimeDelta::Millis(5000);
44
45constexpr float kDefaultLowLossThreshold = 0.02f;
46constexpr float kDefaultHighLossThreshold = 0.1f;
47constexpr DataRate kDefaultBitrateThreshold = DataRate::Zero();
48
49struct UmaRampUpMetric {
50 const char* metric_name;
51 int bitrate_kbps;
52};
53
54const UmaRampUpMetric kUmaRampupMetrics[] = {
55 {"WebRTC.BWE.RampUpTimeTo500kbpsInMs", 500},
56 {"WebRTC.BWE.RampUpTimeTo1000kbpsInMs", 1000},
57 {"WebRTC.BWE.RampUpTimeTo2000kbpsInMs", 2000}};
58const size_t kNumUmaRampupMetrics =
59 sizeof(kUmaRampupMetrics) / sizeof(kUmaRampupMetrics[0]);
60
61const char kBweLosExperiment[] = "WebRTC-BweLossExperiment";
62
63bool BweLossExperimentIsEnabled() {
64 std::string experiment_string =
65 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kBweLosExperiment);
66 // The experiment is enabled iff the field trial string begins with "Enabled".
67 return absl::StartsWith(experiment_string, "Enabled");
68}
69
70bool ReadBweLossExperimentParameters(float* low_loss_threshold,
71 float* high_loss_threshold,
72 uint32_t* bitrate_threshold_kbps) {
73 RTC_DCHECK(low_loss_threshold);
74 RTC_DCHECK(high_loss_threshold);
75 RTC_DCHECK(bitrate_threshold_kbps);
76 std::string experiment_string =
77 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kBweLosExperiment);
78 int parsed_values =
79 sscanf(experiment_string.c_str(), "Enabled-%f,%f,%u", low_loss_threshold,
80 high_loss_threshold, bitrate_threshold_kbps);
81 if (parsed_values == 3) {
82 RTC_CHECK_GT(*low_loss_threshold, 0.0f)
83 << "Loss threshold must be greater than 0.";
84 RTC_CHECK_LE(*low_loss_threshold, 1.0f)
85 << "Loss threshold must be less than or equal to 1.";
86 RTC_CHECK_GT(*high_loss_threshold, 0.0f)
87 << "Loss threshold must be greater than 0.";
88 RTC_CHECK_LE(*high_loss_threshold, 1.0f)
89 << "Loss threshold must be less than or equal to 1.";
90 RTC_CHECK_LE(*low_loss_threshold, *high_loss_threshold)
91 << "The low loss threshold must be less than or equal to the high loss "
92 "threshold.";
93 RTC_CHECK_GE(*bitrate_threshold_kbps, 0)
94 << "Bitrate threshold can't be negative.";
95 RTC_CHECK_LT(*bitrate_threshold_kbps,
96 std::numeric_limits<int>::max() / 1000)
97 << "Bitrate must be smaller enough to avoid overflows.";
98 return true;
99 }
100 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to parse parameters for BweLossExperiment "
101 "experiment from field trial string. Using default.";
102 *low_loss_threshold = kDefaultLowLossThreshold;
103 *high_loss_threshold = kDefaultHighLossThreshold;
104 *bitrate_threshold_kbps = kDefaultBitrateThreshold.kbps();
105 return false;
106}
107} // namespace

109LinkCapacityTracker::LinkCapacityTracker()
110 : tracking_rate("rate", TimeDelta::Seconds(10)) {
111 ParseFieldTrial({&tracking_rate},
112 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-Bwe-LinkCapacity"));
113}
114
115LinkCapacityTracker::~LinkCapacityTracker() {}
116
117void LinkCapacityTracker::UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(
118 Timestamp at_time,
119 DataRate delay_based_bitrate) {
120 if (delay_based_bitrate < last_delay_based_estimate_) {
121 capacity_estimate_bps_ =
122 std::min(capacity_estimate_bps_, delay_based_bitrate.bps<double>());
123 last_link_capacity_update_ = at_time;
124 }
125 last_delay_based_estimate_ = delay_based_bitrate;
126}
127
128void LinkCapacityTracker::OnStartingRate(DataRate start_rate) {
129 if (last_link_capacity_update_.IsInfinite())
130 capacity_estimate_bps_ = start_rate.bps<double>();
131}
132
133void LinkCapacityTracker::OnRateUpdate(absl::optional<DataRate> acknowledged,
134 DataRate target,
135 Timestamp at_time) {
136 if (!acknowledged)
137 return;
138 DataRate acknowledged_target = std::min(*acknowledged, target);
139 if (acknowledged_target.bps() > capacity_estimate_bps_) {
140 TimeDelta delta = at_time - last_link_capacity_update_;
141 double alpha = delta.IsFinite() ? exp(-(delta / tracking_rate.Get())) : 0;
142 capacity_estimate_bps_ = alpha * capacity_estimate_bps_ +
143 (1 - alpha) * acknowledged_target.bps<double>();
144 }
145 last_link_capacity_update_ = at_time;
146}
147
148void LinkCapacityTracker::OnRttBackoff(DataRate backoff_rate,
149 Timestamp at_time) {
150 capacity_estimate_bps_ =
151 std::min(capacity_estimate_bps_, backoff_rate.bps<double>());
152 last_link_capacity_update_ = at_time;
153}
154
155DataRate LinkCapacityTracker::estimate() const {
156 return DataRate::BitsPerSec(capacity_estimate_bps_);
157}
158
159RttBasedBackoff::RttBasedBackoff(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config)
160 : disabled_("Disabled"),
161 configured_limit_("limit", TimeDelta::Seconds(3)),
162 drop_fraction_("fraction", 0.8),
163 drop_interval_("interval", TimeDelta::Seconds(1)),
164 bandwidth_floor_("floor", DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(5)),
165 rtt_limit_(TimeDelta::PlusInfinity()),
166 // By initializing this to plus infinity, we make sure that we never
167 // trigger rtt backoff unless packet feedback is enabled.
168 last_propagation_rtt_update_(Timestamp::PlusInfinity()),
169 last_propagation_rtt_(TimeDelta::Zero()),
170 last_packet_sent_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()) {
171 ParseFieldTrial({&disabled_, &configured_limit_, &drop_fraction_,
172 &drop_interval_, &bandwidth_floor_},
173 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-MaxRttLimit"));
174 if (!disabled_) {
175 rtt_limit_ = configured_limit_.Get();
176 }
177}
178
179void RttBasedBackoff::UpdatePropagationRtt(Timestamp at_time,
180 TimeDelta propagation_rtt) {
181 last_propagation_rtt_update_ = at_time;
182 last_propagation_rtt_ = propagation_rtt;
183}
184
185TimeDelta RttBasedBackoff::CorrectedRtt(Timestamp at_time) const {
186 TimeDelta time_since_rtt = at_time - last_propagation_rtt_update_;
187 TimeDelta timeout_correction = time_since_rtt;
188 // Avoid timeout when no packets are being sent.
189 TimeDelta time_since_packet_sent = at_time - last_packet_sent_;
190 timeout_correction =
191 std::max(time_since_rtt - time_since_packet_sent, TimeDelta::Zero());
192 return timeout_correction + last_propagation_rtt_;
193}
194
195RttBasedBackoff::~RttBasedBackoff() = default;

197SendSideBandwidthEstimation::SendSideBandwidthEstimation(
198 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config,
199 RtcEventLog* event_log)
200 : rtt_backoff_(key_value_config),
201 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_(0),
202 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_(0),
203 current_target_(DataRate::Zero()),
204 last_logged_target_(DataRate::Zero()),
205 min_bitrate_configured_(
206 DataRate::BitsPerSec(congestion_controller::GetMinBitrateBps())),
207 max_bitrate_configured_(kDefaultMaxBitrate),
208 last_low_bitrate_log_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
209 has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_(false),
210 last_loss_feedback_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
211 last_loss_packet_report_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
212 last_fraction_loss_(0),
213 last_logged_fraction_loss_(0),
214 last_round_trip_time_(TimeDelta::Zero()),
215 receiver_limit_(DataRate::PlusInfinity()),
216 delay_based_limit_(DataRate::PlusInfinity()),
217 time_last_decrease_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
218 first_report_time_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
219 initially_lost_packets_(0),
220 bitrate_at_2_seconds_(DataRate::Zero()),
221 uma_update_state_(kNoUpdate),
222 uma_rtt_state_(kNoUpdate),
223 rampup_uma_stats_updated_(kNumUmaRampupMetrics, false),
224 event_log_(event_log),
225 last_rtc_event_log_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
226 low_loss_threshold_(kDefaultLowLossThreshold),
227 high_loss_threshold_(kDefaultHighLossThreshold),
228 bitrate_threshold_(kDefaultBitrateThreshold),
229 loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_(key_value_config),
230 receiver_limit_caps_only_("Enabled") {
231 RTC_DCHECK(event_log);
232 if (BweLossExperimentIsEnabled()) {
233 uint32_t bitrate_threshold_kbps;
234 if (ReadBweLossExperimentParameters(&low_loss_threshold_,
235 &high_loss_threshold_,
236 &bitrate_threshold_kbps)) {
237 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Enabled BweLossExperiment with parameters "
238 << low_loss_threshold_ << ", " << high_loss_threshold_
239 << ", " << bitrate_threshold_kbps;
240 bitrate_threshold_ = DataRate::KilobitsPerSec(bitrate_threshold_kbps);
241 }
242 }
243 ParseFieldTrial({&receiver_limit_caps_only_},
244 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-ReceiverLimitCapsOnly"));
245}

247SendSideBandwidthEstimation::~SendSideBandwidthEstimation() {}

249void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::OnRouteChange() {
250 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
251 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
252 current_target_ = DataRate::Zero();
253 min_bitrate_configured_ =
254 DataRate::BitsPerSec(congestion_controller::GetMinBitrateBps());
255 max_bitrate_configured_ = kDefaultMaxBitrate;
256 last_low_bitrate_log_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
257 has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_ = false;
258 last_loss_feedback_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
259 last_loss_packet_report_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
260 last_fraction_loss_ = 0;
261 last_logged_fraction_loss_ = 0;
262 last_round_trip_time_ = TimeDelta::Zero();
263 receiver_limit_ = DataRate::PlusInfinity();
264 delay_based_limit_ = DataRate::PlusInfinity();
265 time_last_decrease_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
266 first_report_time_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
267 initially_lost_packets_ = 0;
268 bitrate_at_2_seconds_ = DataRate::Zero();
269 uma_update_state_ = kNoUpdate;
270 uma_rtt_state_ = kNoUpdate;
271 last_rtc_event_log_ = Timestamp::MinusInfinity();
272}

274void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::SetBitrates(
275 absl::optional<DataRate> send_bitrate,
276 DataRate min_bitrate,
277 DataRate max_bitrate,
278 Timestamp at_time) {
279 SetMinMaxBitrate(min_bitrate, max_bitrate);
280 if (send_bitrate) {
281 link_capacity_.OnStartingRate(*send_bitrate);
282 SetSendBitrate(*send_bitrate, at_time);
283 }
284}
285
286void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::SetSendBitrate(DataRate bitrate,
287 Timestamp at_time) {
288 RTC_DCHECK_GT(bitrate, DataRate::Zero());
289 // Reset to avoid being capped by the estimate.
290 delay_based_limit_ = DataRate::PlusInfinity();
291 UpdateTargetBitrate(bitrate, at_time);
292 // Clear last sent bitrate history so the new value can be used directly
293 // and not capped.
294 min_bitrate_history_.clear();
295}
296
297void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::SetMinMaxBitrate(DataRate min_bitrate,
298 DataRate max_bitrate) {
299 min_bitrate_configured_ =
300 std::max(min_bitrate, congestion_controller::GetMinBitrate());
301 if (max_bitrate > DataRate::Zero() && max_bitrate.IsFinite()) {
302 max_bitrate_configured_ = std::max(min_bitrate_configured_, max_bitrate);
303 } else {
304 max_bitrate_configured_ = kDefaultMaxBitrate;
305 }
306}
307
308int SendSideBandwidthEstimation::GetMinBitrate() const {
309 return min_bitrate_configured_.bps<int>();
310}
311
312DataRate SendSideBandwidthEstimation::target_rate() const {
313 DataRate target = current_target_;
314 if (receiver_limit_caps_only_)
315 target = std::min(target, receiver_limit_);
316 return std::max(min_bitrate_configured_, target);
317}
318
319DataRate SendSideBandwidthEstimation::GetEstimatedLinkCapacity() const {
320 return link_capacity_.estimate();
321}

323void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateReceiverEstimate(Timestamp at_time,
324 DataRate bandwidth) {
325 // TODO(srte): Ensure caller passes PlusInfinity, not zero, to represent no
326 // limitation.
327 receiver_limit_ = bandwidth.IsZero() ? DataRate::PlusInfinity() : bandwidth;
328 ApplyTargetLimits(at_time);
329}
330
331void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(Timestamp at_time,
332 DataRate bitrate) {
333 link_capacity_.UpdateDelayBasedEstimate(at_time, bitrate);
334 // TODO(srte): Ensure caller passes PlusInfinity, not zero, to represent no
335 // limitation.
336 delay_based_limit_ = bitrate.IsZero() ? DataRate::PlusInfinity() : bitrate;
337 ApplyTargetLimits(at_time);
338}

350void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(
351 const TransportPacketsFeedback& report) {

353 loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.UpdateLossStatistics(

357
358void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdatePacketsLost(int64_t packets_lost,
359 int64_t number_of_packets,
360 Timestamp at_time) {
361 last_loss_feedback_ = at_time;
362 if (first_report_time_.IsInfinite())
363 first_report_time_ = at_time;
364
365 // Check sequence number diff and weight loss report
366 if (number_of_packets > 0) {
367 int64_t expected =
368 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ + number_of_packets;
369
370 // Don't generate a loss rate until it can be based on enough packets.
371 if (expected < kLimitNumPackets) {
372 // Accumulate reports.
373 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = expected;
374 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ += packets_lost;
375 return;
376 }
377
378 has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_ = false;
379 int64_t lost_q8 = (lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ + packets_lost)
380 << 8;
381 last_fraction_loss_ = std::min<int>(lost_q8 / expected, 255);
382
383 // Reset accumulators.
384 lost_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
385 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_ = 0;
386 last_loss_packet_report_ = at_time;
387 UpdateEstimate(at_time);
388 }
389 UpdateUmaStatsPacketsLost(at_time, packets_lost);
390}
391
392void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateUmaStatsPacketsLost(Timestamp at_time,
393 int packets_lost) {
394 DataRate bitrate_kbps =
395 DataRate::KilobitsPerSec((current_target_.bps() + 500) / 1000);
396 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumUmaRampupMetrics; ++i) {
397 if (!rampup_uma_stats_updated_[i] &&
398 bitrate_kbps.kbps() >= kUmaRampupMetrics[i].bitrate_kbps) {
399 RTC_HISTOGRAMS_COUNTS_100000(i, kUmaRampupMetrics[i].metric_name,
400 (at_time - first_report_time_).ms());
401 rampup_uma_stats_updated_[i] = true;
402 }
403 }
404 if (IsInStartPhase(at_time)) {
405 initially_lost_packets_ += packets_lost;
406 } else if (uma_update_state_ == kNoUpdate) {
407 uma_update_state_ = kFirstDone;
408 bitrate_at_2_seconds_ = bitrate_kbps;
409 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("WebRTC.BWE.InitiallyLostPackets",
410 initially_lost_packets_, 0, 100, 50);
411 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("WebRTC.BWE.InitialBandwidthEstimate",
412 bitrate_at_2_seconds_.kbps(), 0, 2000, 50);
413 } else if (uma_update_state_ == kFirstDone &&
414 at_time - first_report_time_ >= kBweConverganceTime) {
415 uma_update_state_ = kDone;
416 int bitrate_diff_kbps = std::max(
417 bitrate_at_2_seconds_.kbps<int>() - bitrate_kbps.kbps<int>(), 0);
418 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("WebRTC.BWE.InitialVsConvergedDiff", bitrate_diff_kbps,
419 0, 2000, 50);
420 }
421}
422
423void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateRtt(TimeDelta rtt, Timestamp at_time) {
424 // Update RTT if we were able to compute an RTT based on this RTCP.
425 // FlexFEC doesn't send RTCP SR, which means we won't be able to compute RTT.
426 if (rtt > TimeDelta::Zero())
427 last_round_trip_time_ = rtt;
428
429 if (!IsInStartPhase(at_time) && uma_rtt_state_ == kNoUpdate) {
430 uma_rtt_state_ = kDone;
431 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS("WebRTC.BWE.InitialRtt", rtt.ms<int>(), 0, 2000, 50);
432 }
433}
434
435void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateEstimate(Timestamp at_time) {
436 if (rtt_backoff_.CorrectedRtt(at_time) > rtt_backoff_.rtt_limit_) {
437 if (at_time - time_last_decrease_ >= rtt_backoff_.drop_interval_ &&
438 current_target_ > rtt_backoff_.bandwidth_floor_) {
439 time_last_decrease_ = at_time;
440 DataRate new_bitrate =
441 std::max(current_target_ * rtt_backoff_.drop_fraction_,
442 rtt_backoff_.bandwidth_floor_.Get());
443 link_capacity_.OnRttBackoff(new_bitrate, at_time);
444 UpdateTargetBitrate(new_bitrate, at_time);
445 return;
446 }
447 // TODO(srte): This is likely redundant in most cases.
448 ApplyTargetLimits(at_time);
449 return;
450 }
451
452 // We trust the REMB and/or delay-based estimate during the first 2 seconds if
453 // we haven't had any packet loss reported, to allow startup bitrate probing.
454 if (last_fraction_loss_ == 0 && IsInStartPhase(at_time)) {
455 DataRate new_bitrate = current_target_;
456 // TODO(srte): We should not allow the new_bitrate to be larger than the
457 // receiver limit here.
458 if (receiver_limit_.IsFinite())
459 new_bitrate = std::max(receiver_limit_, new_bitrate);
460 if (delay_based_limit_.IsFinite())
461 new_bitrate = std::max(delay_based_limit_, new_bitrate);
462 if (loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.Enabled()) {
463 loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.Initialize(new_bitrate);
464 }
465
466 if (new_bitrate != current_target_) {
467 min_bitrate_history_.clear();
468 if (loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.Enabled()) {
469 min_bitrate_history_.push_back(std::make_pair(at_time, new_bitrate));
470 } else {
471 min_bitrate_history_.push_back(
472 std::make_pair(at_time, current_target_));
473 }
474 UpdateTargetBitrate(new_bitrate, at_time);
475 return;
476 }
477 }
478 UpdateMinHistory(at_time);
479 if (last_loss_packet_report_.IsInfinite()) {
480 // No feedback received.
481 // TODO(srte): This is likely redundant in most cases.
482 ApplyTargetLimits(at_time);
483 return;
484 }
485
486 if (loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.InUse()) {
487 DataRate new_bitrate = loss_based_bandwidth_estimation_.Update(
488 at_time, min_bitrate_history_.front().second, delay_based_limit_,
489 last_round_trip_time_);
490 UpdateTargetBitrate(new_bitrate, at_time);
491 return;
492 }
493
494 TimeDelta time_since_loss_packet_report = at_time - last_loss_packet_report_;
495 if (time_since_loss_packet_report < 1.2 * kMaxRtcpFeedbackInterval) {
496 // We only care about loss above a given bitrate threshold.
497 float loss = last_fraction_loss_ / 256.0f;
498 // We only make decisions based on loss when the bitrate is above a
499 // threshold. This is a crude way of handling loss which is uncorrelated
500 // to congestion.
501 if (current_target_ < bitrate_threshold_ || loss <= low_loss_threshold_) {
502 // Loss < 2%: Increase rate by 8% of the min bitrate in the last
503 // kBweIncreaseInterval.
504 // Note that by remembering the bitrate over the last second one can
505 // rampup up one second faster than if only allowed to start ramping
506 // at 8% per second rate now. E.g.:
507 // If sending a constant 100kbps it can rampup immediately to 108kbps
508 // whenever a receiver report is received with lower packet loss.
509 // If instead one would do: current_bitrate_ *= 1.08^(delta time),
510 // it would take over one second since the lower packet loss to achieve
511 // 108kbps.
512 DataRate new_bitrate = DataRate::BitsPerSec(
513 min_bitrate_history_.front().second.bps() * 1.08 + 0.5);
514
515 // Add 1 kbps extra, just to make sure that we do not get stuck
516 // (gives a little extra increase at low rates, negligible at higher
517 // rates).
518 new_bitrate += DataRate::BitsPerSec(1000);
519 UpdateTargetBitrate(new_bitrate, at_time);
520 return;
521 } else if (current_target_ > bitrate_threshold_) {
522 if (loss <= high_loss_threshold_) {
523 // Loss between 2% - 10%: Do nothing.
524 } else {
525 // Loss > 10%: Limit the rate decreases to once a kBweDecreaseInterval
526 // + rtt.
527 if (!has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_ &&
528 (at_time - time_last_decrease_) >=
529 (kBweDecreaseInterval + last_round_trip_time_)) {
530 time_last_decrease_ = at_time;
531
532 // Reduce rate:
533 // newRate = rate * (1 - 0.5*lossRate);
534 // where packetLoss = 256*lossRate;
535 DataRate new_bitrate = DataRate::BitsPerSec(
536 (current_target_.bps() *
537 static_cast<double>(512 - last_fraction_loss_)) /
538 512.0);
539 has_decreased_since_last_fraction_loss_ = true;
540 UpdateTargetBitrate(new_bitrate, at_time);
541 return;
542 }
543 }
544 }
545 }
546 // TODO(srte): This is likely redundant in most cases.
547 ApplyTargetLimits(at_time);
548}

550void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdatePropagationRtt(
551 Timestamp at_time,
552 TimeDelta propagation_rtt) {
553 rtt_backoff_.UpdatePropagationRtt(at_time, propagation_rtt);
554}

556void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::OnSentPacket(const SentPacket& sent_packet) {
557 // Only feedback-triggering packets will be reported here.
558 rtt_backoff_.last_packet_sent_ = sent_packet.send_time;
559}
560
561bool SendSideBandwidthEstimation::IsInStartPhase(Timestamp at_time) const {
562 return first_report_time_.IsInfinite() ||
563 at_time - first_report_time_ < kStartPhase;
564}
565
566void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateMinHistory(Timestamp at_time) {
567 // Remove old data points from history.
568 // Since history precision is in ms, add one so it is able to increase
569 // bitrate if it is off by as little as 0.5ms.
570 while (!min_bitrate_history_.empty() &&
571 at_time - min_bitrate_history_.front().first + TimeDelta::Millis(1) >
572 kBweIncreaseInterval) {
573 min_bitrate_history_.pop_front();
574 }
575
576 // Typical minimum sliding-window algorithm: Pop values higher than current
577 // bitrate before pushing it.
578 while (!min_bitrate_history_.empty() &&
579 current_target_ <= min_bitrate_history_.back().second) {
580 min_bitrate_history_.pop_back();
581 }
582
583 min_bitrate_history_.push_back(std::make_pair(at_time, current_target_));
584}
585
586DataRate SendSideBandwidthEstimation::GetUpperLimit() const {
587 DataRate upper_limit = delay_based_limit_;
588 if (!receiver_limit_caps_only_)
589 upper_limit = std::min(upper_limit, receiver_limit_);
590 upper_limit = std::min(upper_limit, max_bitrate_configured_);
591 return upper_limit;
592}
593
594void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::MaybeLogLowBitrateWarning(DataRate bitrate,
595 Timestamp at_time) {
596 if (at_time - last_low_bitrate_log_ > kLowBitrateLogPeriod) {
597 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Estimated available bandwidth " << ToString(bitrate)
598 << " is below configured min bitrate "
599 << ToString(min_bitrate_configured_) << ".";
600 last_low_bitrate_log_ = at_time;
601 }
602}
603
604void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::MaybeLogLossBasedEvent(Timestamp at_time) {
605 if (current_target_ != last_logged_target_ ||
606 last_fraction_loss_ != last_logged_fraction_loss_ ||
607 at_time - last_rtc_event_log_ > kRtcEventLogPeriod) {
608 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventBweUpdateLossBased>(
609 current_target_.bps(), last_fraction_loss_,
610 expected_packets_since_last_loss_update_));
611 last_logged_fraction_loss_ = last_fraction_loss_;
612 last_logged_target_ = current_target_;
613 last_rtc_event_log_ = at_time;
614 }
615}
616
617void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::UpdateTargetBitrate(DataRate new_bitrate,
618 Timestamp at_time) {
619 new_bitrate = std::min(new_bitrate, GetUpperLimit());
620 if (new_bitrate < min_bitrate_configured_) {
621 MaybeLogLowBitrateWarning(new_bitrate, at_time);
622 new_bitrate = min_bitrate_configured_;
623 }
624 current_target_ = new_bitrate;
625 MaybeLogLossBasedEvent(at_time);
626 link_capacity_.OnRateUpdate(acknowledged_rate_, current_target_, at_time);
627}
628
629void SendSideBandwidthEstimation::ApplyTargetLimits(Timestamp at_time) {
630 UpdateTargetBitrate(current_target_, at_time);
631}
